<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="authority-n">authority <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɔː'θɒrəti/    美 /ə'θɔːrəti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-specialist">1.<strong>权威人士；专家；泰斗 (specialist)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is an <strong>authority on</strong> vocabulary. 
他是词汇研究方面的权威。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>权威；权力；当权</strong></h4>
<p>the power to give orders to people：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Teenagers, when they grow up, begin to question their parents’ authority and wisdom. 
青少年长大的时候，他们会开始怀疑父母的权威和智慧。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In Singapore, rank is important and authority is respected. 
在新加坡等级很重要，人们尊重权威。</p><footer>2014 浙江改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could I speak to someone <strong>in authority</strong> (= who has a position of power) here, please?
我能和这儿主管的人谈谈吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(正式的) 许可；授权</strong></h4>
<p>the official right or permission to do sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>No one may enter <strong>without my authority</strong>. 
未经我许可任何人都不能进入。</p></div>

<h4 id="4-c">4.★ <strong>[C] [常用复数] 官方；当局：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>health authorities</strong> 
卫生当局</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We reported the train accident to <strong>the authorities</strong>.
我们向主管部门报告了这起火车事故。</p></div></div>